Issues.Body:
Currently, when there is an error inside a lazy loaded component constructor an unhandled promise rejection is thrown which causes the error handler not to be invoked on the server due to an issue with Zone.js see https://github.com/angular/angular/issues/49930.

While this is a workaround for that in general we should not cause unhandled promise rejections and always await and catch promises especially going for going zoneless, this is because Node.js does not wait for pending unhandled promises and these will cause the process to exit. See: https://github.com/nodejs/node/issues/22088

Eventually, the framework will need to be updated to better handle  promises in certain listeners for zoneless and avoid unhandled promises

Example on potential problematic code.
```ts
{
    provide: APP_BOOTSTRAP_LISTENER,
    useFactory: () => {
      Promise.resolve().then(() => {})
    },
}
```

This change is also a step closer to address https://github.com/angular/angular/issues/33642

